11
00:00:57,930 --> 00:01:00,060
<i>[Life with Sweets]</i>

12
00:01:00,066 --> 00:01:03,086
You should write about the brand concept in detail,

13
00:01:03,086 --> 00:01:06,326
especially about why the candy is shaped like lip cream.

14
00:01:06,326 --> 00:01:09,366
It's better to enlarge the photo for a greater impact.

15
00:01:09,366 --> 00:01:11,666
I see. I know what to do now.

16
00:01:11,666 --> 00:01:12,827
I'll leave it to you then.

17
00:01:12,827 --> 00:01:14,327
No problem.

18
00:01:14,956 --> 00:01:19,999
- Actually, we saw your boyfriend buying a ring yesterday.
- What?

19
00:01:19,999 --> 00:01:23,196
Even from afar, I could see that the stone on the ring is big.

20
00:01:23,196 --> 00:01:25,166
That must be your engagement ring.

21
00:01:25,166 --> 00:01:29,196
Both of you entered the advertising agency at the same time, right?

22
00:01:29,196 --> 00:01:31,086
What an outstanding couple.

23
00:01:31,086 --> 00:01:35,486
I think her boyfriend would want to keep it a secret.

24
00:01:35,486 --> 00:01:37,126
I see.

25
00:01:37,126 --> 00:01:39,536
When your boyfriend says "Surprise!",

26
00:01:39,536 --> 00:01:41,676
please pretend that you are surprised.

27
00:01:41,676 --> 00:01:43,947
- I'll do that.
- Good.

28
00:01:44,926 --> 00:01:49,356
Ichita is a perfect man to marry.

29
00:01:49,356 --> 00:01:52,066
But I wish that he can take the initiative during our dates.

30
00:01:52,066 --> 00:01:54,386
He always asks, "Where do you want to go?" or "What do you want to eat?"

31
00:01:54,386 --> 00:01:56,686
So, I have to decide in the end.

32
00:01:56,686 --> 00:02:00,006
<i>I also hope he can contact me more frequently.</i>

33
00:02:00,006 --> 00:02:01,916
<i>The other time, when I had realized, it was already three days.</i>

34
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:03,886
<i>Three days without any calls or messages.</i>

35
00:02:03,886 --> 00:02:06,916
And I hope he would say something like "Come to me. I will protect you."

36
00:02:06,916 --> 00:02:09,596
Such words sound so manly.

37
00:02:09,596 --> 00:02:12,626
And I do not intend to stop working after getting married.

38
00:02:12,626 --> 00:02:16,146
Ichita always says, "If you work harder, you can advance further in your career." Therefore...

39
00:02:16,146 --> 00:02:18,156
<i>You talk too much.</i>

40
00:02:18,156 --> 00:02:21,106
Stop turning your dried squid and eat it.

41
00:02:21,106 --> 00:02:23,556
<i>When you were in high school,</i>

42
00:02:23,556 --> 00:02:25,296
you were not popular at all.

43
00:02:25,296 --> 00:02:27,113
- W-Wait a minute.
- I mean...

44
00:02:27,113 --> 00:02:30,016
you were a hard worker who was not popular or in the limelight.

45
00:02:30,016 --> 00:02:33,856
<i>But your love debuted in university and had a few relationships.</i>

46
00:02:33,856 --> 00:02:36,166
<i>However, things did not go well.</i>

47
00:02:36,166 --> 00:02:39,856
And it's the same for your current boyfriend.

48
00:02:39,856 --> 00:02:42,386
So, what is your ideal boyfriend?

49
00:02:42,386 --> 00:02:44,216
Do you just want to say such a man doesn't exist?

50
00:02:44,216 --> 00:02:45,176
<i>No.</i>

51
00:02:45,176 --> 00:02:48,776
I think Nozomu Jinguji is the one.

52
00:02:49,536 --> 00:02:50,936
Why mention him suddenly?

53
00:02:50,936 --> 00:02:54,736
17 years old. Your first love came late.

54
00:02:54,736 --> 00:02:57,646
<i>It must be memorable.</i>

55
00:03:00,706 --> 00:03:02,586
<i>Way to go, Jinguji!</i>

56
00:03:02,586 --> 00:03:04,966
<i>Nice shoot, Jinguji!</i>

57
00:03:10,216 --> 00:03:13,026
<i>Murai, where are you going after this?</i>

58
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:15,256
<i>- I'm going for training,
- I see.</i>

59
00:03:15,256 --> 00:03:17,496
<i>so that I would be able to eat Ms. Tanaka's cheeks.</i>

60
00:03:17,496 --> 00:03:19,446
<i>- Let's go back together.
- Okay.</i>

61
00:03:19,446 --> 00:03:21,116
<i>What are you going to do when you get home?</i>

62
00:03:21,116 --> 00:03:22,097
<i>Gaming.</i>

63
00:03:22,097 --> 00:03:24,467
<i>I want to play games with you, too!</i>

64
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:26,756
<i>- Do you want to come?
- Yes!</i>

65
00:03:26,756 --> 00:03:31,976
<i>But your first love is a delusion and fantasy.</i>

66
00:03:31,976 --> 00:03:33,096
Do you know?

67
00:03:33,096 --> 00:03:37,866
Jinguji got married in Brazil to a Latin woman, and they already have three children.

68
00:03:37,866 --> 00:03:40,866
<i>And he's so fat now. Everything is in the past now.</i>

69
00:03:40,866 --> 00:03:42,716
Stop. Don't say anymore.

70
00:03:42,716 --> 00:03:47,006
Anyway, getting an ideal boyfriend is not realistic.

71
00:03:47,006 --> 00:03:49,566
Therefore, don't compare him with your future partner.

72
00:03:49,566 --> 00:03:53,006
<i>Sawamura is a good catch.</i>

73
00:03:53,006 --> 00:03:56,096
<i>If he were to propose, you should accept it with thanks.</i>

74
00:03:56,096 --> 00:03:57,686
Face the reality. You can't get away from it.

75
00:03:57,686 --> 00:04:01,086
I know that. I will reply him properly.

76
00:04:01,716 --> 00:04:03,566
Mama, there's no towel.

77
00:04:03,566 --> 00:04:06,066
Okay! Sorry, I'll call again.

78
00:04:06,066 --> 00:04:07,616
See you.

79
00:04:08,216 --> 00:04:10,576
<i>Tomomi, she had a boyfriend then.</i>

80
00:04:10,576 --> 00:04:13,506
<i>She knew that her boyfriend was having flings with his ex, but she did not say anything.</i>

81
00:04:13,506 --> 00:04:15,226
<i>She pretended not to know anything.</i>

82
00:04:15,226 --> 00:04:18,986
<i>Without prying, she predicted that this investment would be fruitful.</i>

83
00:04:18,986 --> 00:04:21,976
<i>And it came true when she got married.</i>

84
00:04:22,556 --> 00:04:28,066
Tomomi, she's always been a practical person since high school.
<i>[How to earn money by day trading as a stay-home mom?]</i>

85
00:04:28,966 --> 00:04:32,096
Nozomu Jinguji...

86
00:04:33,806 --> 00:04:38,272
<i>Yumeko Onodera will be the conductor of the choir competition.</i>

87
00:04:38,272 --> 00:04:40,086
<i>Please clap for her!</i>

88
00:04:40,086 --> 00:04:44,706
<i>Why... I do not have any experience in music.</i>

89
00:05:00,220 --> 00:05:02,870
<i>[Searching for Lost Time]</i>

90
00:05:30,746 --> 00:05:32,436
<i>Good luck.</i>

91
00:05:41,436 --> 00:05:43,656
<i>This first love which came late...</i>

92
00:05:43,656 --> 00:05:49,817
<i>like what my close friends say, maybe it has never left me.</i>

93
00:05:51,396 --> 00:05:53,276
What is this about?

94
00:05:54,336 --> 00:05:55,526
It's all my fault.

95
00:05:55,526 --> 00:05:59,506
Yukiko Saeki's chocolate was supposed to be sent to the Fukuoka event,

96
00:05:59,506 --> 00:06:02,506
but due to Sayuki's mistake, it was sent here.

97
00:06:02,506 --> 00:06:04,646
Please... don't blame it on me totally.

98
00:06:04,646 --> 00:06:06,376
Because you were the one who wrote the purchase order.

99
00:06:06,376 --> 00:06:08,586
This should be the team's mistake.

100
00:06:08,586 --> 00:06:12,226
That means it's my mistake.

101
00:06:12,226 --> 00:06:15,316
These limited ten pieces ordered by Yumeko,

102
00:06:15,316 --> 00:06:18,966
are finally completed to be the company's featured product.

103
00:06:18,966 --> 00:06:20,626
I will deliver them.

104
00:06:20,626 --> 00:06:22,336
What?

105
00:06:22,336 --> 00:06:25,206
- If I go now, I should be able to reach in the afternoon.
- I should do it.

106
00:06:25,206 --> 00:06:26,736
They know who I am.

107
00:06:26,736 --> 00:06:29,126
So it will be better for me to go and apologize to them.

108
00:06:29,126 --> 00:06:30,337
<i>We're sorry.</i>

109
00:06:30,337 --> 00:06:32,807
Don't worry. Just leave it to me.

110
00:06:35,286 --> 00:06:37,256
I'm really sorry about this matter.

111
00:06:37,256 --> 00:06:41,630
I will be there to settle the problem personally.

112
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:43,040
Yes.

113
00:06:43,046 --> 00:06:45,286
Sorry to keep you waiting, Ms. Onodera.

114
00:06:45,286 --> 00:06:46,896
- Please have a good trip.
- Thank you.

115
00:06:46,896 --> 00:06:47,826
Thank you very much.

116
00:06:47,826 --> 00:06:49,726
It was still here just now!

117
00:06:49,726 --> 00:06:51,346
Please wait a while.

118
00:06:51,845 --> 00:06:55,086
- It's definitely here!
- Sir, are you okay?

119
00:06:55,086 --> 00:06:57,972
- Please wait a while.
- Excuse me, can I help you?

120
00:06:59,716 --> 00:07:01,196
Jinguji?

121
00:07:01,196 --> 00:07:02,386
What?

122
00:07:02,386 --> 00:07:05,125
<i>It can't be. Jinguji is in Brazil.</i>

123
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:07,926
<i>And he looks too young.</i>

124
00:07:07,926 --> 00:07:11,276
Sorry, I need to go back to my hometown on this flight.

125
00:07:11,276 --> 00:07:13,556
My grandmother is in critical condition.

126
00:07:13,556 --> 00:07:17,006
She's my only family member.

127
00:07:17,006 --> 00:07:18,506
That's why...

128
00:07:19,646 --> 00:07:22,956
The wallet with the ticket fee was definitely in the bag!

129
00:07:25,146 --> 00:07:27,776
Can't you do anything to help?

130
00:07:27,776 --> 00:07:30,116
I will definitely pay back the 50,000 yen <i>($365)</i>.

131
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:32,476
Excuse me. You can have this.

132
00:07:33,116 --> 00:07:34,036
What?

133
00:07:34,036 --> 00:07:35,956
Please take it and go to your grandmother's.

134
00:07:35,956 --> 00:07:37,424
No, I cannot...

135
00:07:37,424 --> 00:07:39,106
It's fine.

136
00:07:39,106 --> 00:07:41,646
I need to go and catch my flight.

137
00:07:42,236 --> 00:07:45,056
Excuse me! Thank you very much.

138
00:07:45,056 --> 00:07:46,433
I will return the money. Can I have your contact?

139
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:48,076
Don't bother.

140
00:07:48,076 --> 00:07:50,466
I'm happy to see you.

141
00:07:52,670 --> 00:07:57,050
‚ô´ <i>I was able to overcome my trembling sorrow</i> ‚ô´

142
00:07:57,050 --> 00:08:00,766
<i>It sounds good to help a young person in trouble,</i>

143
00:08:00,766 --> 00:08:04,246
<i>but to give 50,000 yen to someone who looks like my first love,</i>

144
00:08:04,246 --> 00:08:07,026
<i>Tomomi is sure to get angry with me.</i>

145
00:08:07,754 --> 00:08:09,756
<i>Jinguji?</i>

146
00:08:09,756 --> 00:08:13,923
<i>They really look alike.</i>

147
00:08:13,923 --> 00:08:17,140
‚ô´ <i>So let's simply believe</i> ‚ô´

148
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:19,216
‚ô´ <i>Yes, like that</i> ‚ô´

149
00:08:19,216 --> 00:08:23,670
‚ô´ <i>Hey, see? Gratitude builds in a crescendo</i> ‚ô´

150
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:27,780
‚ô´ <i>from this world I live with you</i> ‚ô´

151
00:08:27,780 --> 00:08:33,247
‚ô´ <i>I thank you for giving me the willpower I need</i> ‚ô´

152
00:08:33,247 --> 00:08:37,697
‚ô´ <i>Now my gratitude builds in a crescendo</i> ‚ô´
<i>[Ideal Boyfriend]</i>

153
00:08:38,466 --> 00:08:39,866
President!

154
00:08:40,426 --> 00:08:41,766
Good morning.

155
00:08:41,766 --> 00:08:42,966
<i>[Episode 1]</i>

156
00:08:42,966 --> 00:08:44,406
Don't call me that.

157
00:08:44,406 --> 00:08:46,316
Mizukami, my senior.

158
00:08:46,316 --> 00:08:48,466
The event was carried out smoothly.

159
00:08:48,466 --> 00:08:50,226
Sorry to have made you worried.

160
00:08:50,226 --> 00:08:51,966
Thank you for making the effort to deliver the products.

161
00:08:51,966 --> 00:08:55,346
The client wrote me an email to thank me for the event.

162
00:08:55,346 --> 00:08:56,996
I'm glad to hear that.

163
00:08:56,996 --> 00:08:58,496
Onodera.

164
00:08:59,346 --> 00:09:01,218
Can I have a moment?

165
00:09:02,643 --> 00:09:05,378
Power harassment? Me?

166
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:09,613
I don't think there's a problem with your management.

167
00:09:09,613 --> 00:09:14,273
You are better than anyone in your work performance.

168
00:09:14,273 --> 00:09:16,883
But due to the complaint,

169
00:09:16,883 --> 00:09:19,773
I need to have an official talk with you.

170
00:09:19,773 --> 00:09:23,331
Any disagreement or misunderstanding must be resolved.

171
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:26,773
Who made the complaint?

172
00:09:28,355 --> 00:09:32,883
<i>Forcing to work beyond the hours stated by the Labor Standards,</i>

173
00:09:32,883 --> 00:09:37,243
<i>being blamed for the superior's mistake,</i>

174
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:40,953
<i>being removed from work against one's will, etc.</i>

175
00:09:40,953 --> 00:09:43,303
<i>I can't work together with her anymore.</i>

176
00:09:43,303 --> 00:09:46,343
<i>It's beyond me.</i>

177
00:09:52,073 --> 00:09:53,963
Are you all right?

178
00:09:53,963 --> 00:09:57,123
Huh? Why?

179
00:09:57,653 --> 00:10:00,113
Jinguji?

180
00:10:02,550 --> 00:10:04,580
Are you all right?

181
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:07,760
Thank you so much.

182
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:22,380
Can I know...

183
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:27,510
why are you...

184
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:32,620
I was waiting for you in front of your company.

185
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:37,880
It's the paper bag that you were carrying. That's how I knew about your company.

186
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,720
Paper bag?

187
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:45,130
I remember the paper bag in your hands at the airport.

188
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:50,150
Don't tell me you've been waiting all this time?

189
00:10:50,830 --> 00:10:52,031
About five hours.

190
00:10:52,031 --> 00:10:53,551
That long?!

191
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:57,300
I gave you that money.

192
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:01,210
Therefore, you don't need to come on purpose to return it.

193
00:11:01,780 --> 00:11:03,590
For that...

194
00:11:06,890 --> 00:11:08,720
I'm sorry.

195
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,220
What?

196
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:14,250
I don't think I can return the money immediately.

197
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:17,100
During that time, I gathered all the money that I had,

198
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:20,930
and put them into the wallet for the flight.

199
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:23,790
But I lost the wallet.

200
00:11:23,790 --> 00:11:27,930
In other words, I don't think I can pay back the money.

201
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:31,220
I'm really sorry.

202
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:34,170
Don't worry.

203
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:37,410
I didn't expect you to return the money at all.

204
00:11:37,410 --> 00:11:39,320
So, don't worry about it.

205
00:11:40,268 --> 00:11:46,089
Although... I cannot return the money immediately,

206
00:11:46,089 --> 00:11:48,660
can I do anything for you in return?

207
00:11:48,660 --> 00:11:51,530
Please tell me what you want me to do.

208
00:11:51,530 --> 00:11:55,020
Wait, you don't have to do this.

209
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:05,700
It's all thanks to you that I was able to see my grandmother before she passed away.

210
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:09,581
I don't have any parents.

211
00:12:09,581 --> 00:12:12,051
My grandmother raised me.

212
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:17,120
If I did not see her for the last time,

213
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:20,060
I would've probably regretted it for the rest of my life.

214
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:23,530
Therefore...

215
00:12:24,490 --> 00:12:27,010
I am indebted to you.

216
00:12:28,730 --> 00:12:32,420
Please let me do something for you. I beg you.

217
00:12:32,420 --> 00:12:36,570
I can feel what you are trying to convey.

218
00:12:36,570 --> 00:12:39,170
So, please forget about the money.

219
00:12:39,170 --> 00:12:42,060
- But I won't feel-
- It's really okay.

220
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:46,500
<i>They really look alike.</i>

221
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:50,137
By the way,

222
00:12:50,137 --> 00:12:55,157
you are not related in any way to a person named Nozomu Jinguji, right?

223
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:58,670
Sorry, please forget what I said.

224
00:13:02,410 --> 00:13:06,680
<i>During high school, my classmates would go on dates at the amusement park.</i>

225
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:09,380
<i>But I just had my head in books.</i>

226
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:13,400
<i>To have a date at the amusement park was something unimaginable.</i>

227
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:16,200
<i>It would only happen in my dreams.</i>

228
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:19,300
If you want to do something for me,

229
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:21,500
can I have a request?

230
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,910
Yes, of course.

231
00:13:26,070 --> 00:13:29,770
That! Can you go on a ride with me together?

232
00:13:29,770 --> 00:13:31,170
What?

233
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:38,630
<i>If I was was with Jinguji, would I be feeling this way?</i>

234
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:46,150
<i>Come over here.</i>

235
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:47,960
<i>Just come here.</i>

236
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:54,640
<i>Don't let go of my hand until I say so.</i>

237
00:13:56,370 --> 00:13:58,110
<i>I won't let go.</i>

238
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:01,870
<i>Forever and ever.</i>

239
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:06,850
Excuse me.

240
00:14:06,850 --> 00:14:08,920
Are you all right?

241
00:14:10,679 --> 00:14:13,700
<i>Oh no! The fantasy was too overwhelming.</i>

242
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,938
<i>I am going to get marry soon.</i>

243
00:14:15,938 --> 00:14:18,658
<i>What exactly am I doing?</i>

244
00:14:19,940 --> 00:14:22,820
I came to return the money to you,

